    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 1406,
      "versionNonce": 2111836537,
      "index": "aO",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "SAbtP459iG0lBHj-i5f2t",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 1723.9956330109671,
      "y": 489.1070864508931,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "width": 899.5465066061012,
      "height": 599.9454290744844,
      "seed": 2036180224,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1722229362463,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 21.816197420890337,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "text": "Algorithm : -\n\n1 - first have a hash-map to combine position with indexed\n    to compare the positions with its indexes and directions\n\n2 - then initiate the stack\n\n3 - initiate both directions and indexes of robots in the same loop\n\n4 - check if direction[i] == \"R\" append to stack\n\n5 - Else while appending check whether n and n-1 have opposite direction \n\n6 - if yes then check the health of both \n\n7 - if health are same pop both health = 0 \n\n8 - if one is less then pop the robot with less health and decrement other by 1\n\n9 - if one is greater then pop the robot with less health and decrement other by 1\n\n10 - by the end of the program return robot with remaining health != 0",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Algorithm : -\n\n1 - first have a hash-map to combine position with indexed\n    to compare the positions with its indexes and directions\n\n2 - then initiate the stack\n\n3 - initiate both directions and indexes of robots in the same loop\n\n4 - check if direction[i] == \"R\" append to stack\n\n5 - Else while appending check whether n and n-1 have opposite direction \n\n6 - if yes then check the health of both \n\n7 - if health are same pop both health = 0 \n\n8 - if one is less then pop the robot with less health and decrement other by 1\n\n9 - if one is greater then pop the robot with less health and decrement other by 1\n\n10 - by the end of the program return robot with remaining health != 0",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 1092,
      "versionNonce": 388155193,
      "index": "aP",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "fRddD8qBe6snIPeMzdsE1",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 1708.2167330119478,
      "y": 47.46728718834609,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "width": 760.4714457770306,
      "height": 379.3796641614615,
      "seed": 1847567616,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1722229365485,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 21.67883795208351,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "text": "Edge cases : - \n\n1 - If both robots have same health when collide pop both\n\n2 - if 0 survivors return empty array\n\n3 - if two robot collide the robot with lower health is removed\n\n     from the line and health of the other robot will decreases by one\n\n4 - what if a robot will move in a left direction \n    it will never collide with someone but if the previous\n     robot only going to the right then a only then\n",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Edge cases : - \n\n1 - If both robots have same health when collide pop both\n\n2 - if 0 survivors return empty array\n\n3 - if two robot collide the robot with lower health is removed\n\n     from the line and health of the other robot will decreases by one\n\n4 - what if a robot will move in a left direction \n    it will never collide with someone but if the previous\n     robot only going to the right then a only then\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
